        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 12 at 3:15PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 315 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Columbus, or over Tryon, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Columbus, Tryon, Mill Spring, and Gowensville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
